  • Method Details

    • selectRows

      public DataCol selectRows​(java.lang.String from, java.lang.String to)
      Returns a new DataCol composed of the rows between the specified from and to indexes inclusive.

      If one of the two indexes does not exist - returns empty DC. If from is placed below the index to - returns empty DC. Otherwise, return the DataCol containing the required selection of rows.

      Parameters:
      from - - starting index
      to - - ending index
      Returns:
      the new DataCol

    • selectRows

      public DataCol selectRows​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> indexes)
      Returns a new DataCol composed of the rows associated to the specified indexes. If indexes are not valid or null, returns an empty DC.
      Parameters:
      indexes - - list of indexes
      Returns:
      the new DataCol
